13 Large species, body about 3.5–5 mm long. Frontal bristles present. Scutum dull, not at least shining, dull grey, often with black stripes, or mostly black (or even subshining in some lights). Antennal stylus short, half as long as 3 rd segment, or not much longer (except for
H. anglodanica
)...................................................................... 14

- Male : fore basitarsus very large, as long as tibia, and dorsally clothed with long bristly hairs; mid basitarsus simple, without a sensory brush at base posteriorly. Scutum differently striped, and acrostichals and dorsocentrals smaller, hair-like. Female : hind tibia simple and slender (
H. veneta
) or very thickened (
H. megalochira
